President Biden addressed Megan Rapinoe and Margaret Purce, members of the U.S. Women's National Soccer Team, in a speech at the South Court Auditorium. He thanked them and their team for inspiring their daughters and granddaughters and for advocating for fair pay and decency. The President highlighted the gender pay gap and emphasized that women still earn less than men in nearly every job. He discussed the impact of the pandemic on women, particularly women of color, who are on the frontlines as essential workers but still earn less. President Biden mentioned the American Rescue Plan and its provisions to address the pay gap and support women and families. He called on Congress to pass the Paycheck Fairness Act and increase pay transparency. The President emphasized the importance of equal pay for women and how it benefits families and the economy. He concluded by signing a proclamation naming Equal Pay Day 2021 as a commitment to seek equal pay and build back better.